article.story: CHARLOTTE, N.C. -- — Giancarlo Rosado and Nik Graves had 12 points apiece in Charlotte's 60-54 victory against Gardner-Webb on Tuesday night. Rosado added eight rebounds and five assists for the 49ers (3-1). Graves shot 3 of 14 from the floor, including 1 for 5 from 3-point range, and 5 for 6 from the line. Robert Braswell went 4 of 7 from the field (2 for 4 from 3-point range) to finish with 11 points. The Runnin' Bulldogs (2-3) were led by Anthony Selden, who posted 12 points and four blocks. Gardner-Webb also got 12 points from Shahar Lazar. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
